FBIS3-55554 "drsov006_b_94033" FBIS-SOV-94-006 Document Type:Daily Report 10 Jan 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political Issues Deputies To Demand Report on White House Repair Costs LD0901145894 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1327 GMT 9 Jan 94 LD0901145894 Moscow INTERFAX Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Representatives of the State Duma's influential factions intend to demand a detailed report on government spending on repairing the White House. Deputies of a major parliamentary faction told Interfax that the rubles and hard-currency reserved for buying building materials, equipment and furniture had been mishandled. According to some estimates, spending on the restoration and construction work alone amounts to $75 Mn-$85 Mn. The work is done round the clock by Russia builders and their Turkish colleagues from the companies Enka and Gama.
